=3D"pageContent"><article><div class=3D"artText"><div class=3D"section1"><d=
iv class=3D"Normal">This <a href=3D"https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/to=
pic/age-calculator" target=3D"_blank">age calculator</a> has been designed =
to calculate your <a href=3D"https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/topic/cur=
rent-age" target=3D"_blank">current age</a> based on the input provided in =
the =E2=80=98<a href=3D"https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/topic/Date-of-=
Birth" target=3D"_blank">Date of Birth</a>=E2=80=99 field. Alternatively, y=
ou can enter a date of your choice in the =E2=80=98Current Age or <a href=
=3D"https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/topic/Age-as-of" target=3D"_blank"=
>Age as of</a>=E2=80=99 field to know your age at that particular point in =
time.<br><br>Additionally, this <a href=3D"https://economictimes.indiatimes=
.com/topic/calculator" target=3D"_blank">calculator</a> can be used to dete=
rmine the age of things such as a historical monument or a vintage/collecta=
ble item. For such calculations, enter the date on which the construction o=
f the monument was completed or when the collectable item was procured in t=
he =E2=80=98Date of Birth=E2=80=99 field and the present date in the =E2=80=
=98Current Age or Age as of=E2=80=99 field to calculate the age of the monu=
ment or the item. <br><br>The calculator displays the age in terms of years=
, months and days. It also has a =E2=80=98Singular Expression=E2=80=99 sect=
ion where the calculation is shown in months, weeks, days, hours, minutes, =
and seconds. <br><br><strong>What is an age calculator?</strong><br>An age =
calculator is a digital tool that can be used to calculate the age of a per=
son, place or thing, based on the information provided in the calculator.<b=
r><br><strong>How to use this age calculator?</strong><br>By default, the c=
alculator shows the present date in both the =E2=80=98Date of Birth=E2=80=
=99 and the =E2=80=98Current Age or Age as of=E2=80=99 field. <br><br>To ca=
lculate your current age or that of an object/thing, fill the =E2=80=98Date=
 of Birth=E2=80=99 field with relevant details and leave the =E2=80=98Curre=
nt Age or Age as of=E2=80=99 field as it is. On the other hand, to know how=
 old you were or would be at a certain point in time, fill the =E2=80=98Dat=
e of Birth=E2=80=99 field with relevant details and enter the required date=
 in the =E2=80=98Current Age or Age as of=E2=80=99 field. This process can =
also be followed to determine the age of a place or thing as of a certain d=
ate.<br><br>Here is a list of the steps that need to be followed to operate=
 this calculator:<br><ol><li>First, select the relevant month, date, and ye=
ar from their respective drop-down menus in the =E2=80=98Date of Birth=E2=
=80=99 field</li><li>Now, fill the =E2=80=98Current Age or Age as of=E2=80=
=99 field by selecting the relevant month, date, and year from their respec=
tive drop-down menus or leave the field as it is (as per your requirement)<=
/li><li>Then click on the =E2=80=98CALCULATE=E2=80=99 button to get the res=
ult</li><li>To make a new calculation, click on the =E2=80=98Clear=E2=80=99=
 button to reset the calculator and enter new data, as per your requirement=
</li></ol><br><strong>What does the output page of this calculator show?</s=
trong><br><ol><li>The output page has two sections:</li><li>The main output=
 section displays the age in terms of years, months, and days or as is appl=
icable</li><li>The =E2=80=98Singular Expression=E2=80=99 section segregates=
 the whole duration/age and displays it either in terms of months and days =
or weeks and days or only days or hours or minutes or seconds</li></ol><br>=
<strong>How does this age calculator work?</strong><br>India, as a country,=
 is an amalgamation of cultures where various types of traditional calendar=
s are followed. Prominent among them include the Saka Samvat, Vikram Samvat=
, and the Hijri calendar. But, when it comes to official purposes, the Greg=
orian calendar is the calendar used in India as well as various countries a=
round the world. <br><br>This calculator also uses the Gregorian calendar t=
o make calculations. A year is divided into 365 days in this calendar, exce=
pt for a leap year, which has 366 days. The total number of days in a calen=
dar year is categorized into 12 months of varying lengths. Each month eithe=
r has 30 or 31 days, except February which has 28 days in a normal year and=
 29 days in a leap year. <br><br>The system used by this calculator is the =
most commonly used age system. In this calculator, a person=E2=80=99s age s=
tarts from zero and the person turns one year old only after 12 months have=
 passed. Similarly, in any type of age calculation here, the age is increas=
ed by one year after the completion of 12 months from the birth date/start =
date. <br><br><strong>What role does time zone play in the process of age c=
alculation?</strong><br>Though the time zone doesn=E2=80=99t play a signifi=
cant role in age calculation, this calculator can detect the user's time zo=
ne and display the required age accordingly. <br> <br><br></div></div></div=
